	<LEVEL style-name="Chapter" style-name-escaped="Chapter" style-id="0-0-0-685" level-depth="2" toc-section="false">
		<RECORD id="0-0-0-235940" number="50209" version="2307">
			<HEADING>Chapter 41: Distribution of Materials on Water Safety</HEADING>
			<PARA>
				<DESTINATION id="0-0-0-28576" name="T21-aC041"/>Chapter 41: Distribution of Materials on Water Safety</PARA>
		</RECORD>
		<LEVEL style-name="Subchapter" style-name-escaped="Subchapter" style-id="0-0-0-688" level-depth="3" toc-section="false">
			<LEVEL style-name="Appendix" style-name-escaped="Appendix" style-id="0-0-0-691" level-depth="4" toc-section="false">
				<LEVEL style-name="Part" style-name-escaped="Part" style-id="0-0-0-694" level-depth="5" toc-section="false">
					<LEVEL style-name="Article" style-name-escaped="Article" style-id="0-0-0-697" level-depth="6" toc-section="false">
						<LEVEL style-name="Subarticle" style-name-escaped="Subarticle" style-id="0-0-0-700" level-depth="7" toc-section="false">
							<LEVEL style-name="Subarticle - Part" style-name-escaped="Subarticle---Part" style-id="0-0-0-29474" level-depth="8" toc-section="false">
								<LEVEL style-name="Section" style-name-escaped="Section" style-id="0-0-0-703" level-depth="9" toc-section="true">
									<RECORD id="0-0-0-236169" number="50210" version="2307">
										<HEADING>§ 21-1013 Distribution of materials on water safety.</HEADING>
										<PARA>
											<DESTINATION id="0-0-0-28578" name="21-1013"/>§ 21-1013 Distribution of materials on water safety.</PARA>
									</RECORD>
									<LEVEL style-name="Normal Level" style-name-escaped="Normal-Level" style-id="0-0-0-0" level-depth="0" toc-section="false">
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-236168" number="50211" version="2307">
											<PARA>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>a.<TAB tab-count="1"/>
												<CHARFORMAT bold="0" italic="1" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Definitions.</CHARFORMAT> As used in this chapter, the following terms have the following meanings: <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-117]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-236164" number="50212" version="2298">
											<PARA>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>
												<CHARFORMAT bold="1" italic="0" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">School.</CHARFORMAT> The term “school” means a school of the city school district of the city of New York. <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-117]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-236163" number="50213" version="2298">
											<PARA>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>
												<CHARFORMAT bold="1" italic="0" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Student.</CHARFORMAT> The term “student” means a pupil who is a student as defined in section <LINK style-name="Jump" style-name-escaped="Jump" style-id="0-0-0-23" type="Jump" destination-name="21-950" destination-id="0-0-0-9703">21-950</LINK>, a child who is enrolled in an early education center with which the department contracts to provide pre-kindergarten, or a child who is enrolled in a free full-day early education program for 3-year-old children offered by the department. <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-117]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-236162" number="50214" version="2301">
											<PARA>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>b.<TAB tab-count="1"/>
												<CHARFORMAT bold="0" italic="1" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Written materials.</CHARFORMAT> No later than August 1, 2026, the department of parks and recreation shall develop written materials containing information about water safety and drowning prevention. Such department shall update the content of such materials each year to reflect changes in best practices for water safety and drowning prevention. Such materials shall include, but need not be limited to, the following: <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-117]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-236161" number="50215" version="2298">
											<PARA>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>1.<TAB tab-count="1"/>Water safety practices, including drowning prevention techniques; <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-117]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-236160" number="50216" version="2298">
											<PARA>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>2.<TAB tab-count="1"/>Information on swimming lessons and other water safety programming offered by such department; and <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-117]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-236159" number="50217" version="2298">
											<PARA>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>3.<TAB tab-count="1"/>Any additional information deemed relevant by such department. <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-117]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-236157" number="50218" version="2298">
											<PARA>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>c.<TAB tab-count="1"/>
												<CHARFORMAT bold="0" italic="1" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Publication and distribution.</CHARFORMAT>&#160;<HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-117]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-236158" number="50219" version="2298">
											<PARA>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>1.<TAB tab-count="1"/>The department shall post the written materials developed pursuant to this section on its website. <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-117]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-236156" number="50220" version="2298">
											<PARA>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>2.<TAB tab-count="1"/>The department of parks and recreation shall provide the department with the written materials developed pursuant to this section. The department shall distribute such materials to each school, to be shared with every student of each school, at the beginning and end of each academic year. <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-117]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-236153" number="50221" version="2307">
											<PARA>(L.L. 2026/006, 1/3/2026, eff. 1/3/2026; Am. L.L. 2026/016, 1/17/2026, eff. 1/17/2026) <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-117]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
									</LEVEL>
								</LEVEL>
							</LEVEL>
						</LEVEL>
					</LEVEL>
				</LEVEL>
			</LEVEL>
		</LEVEL>
	</LEVEL>
</DOCUMENT>